[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating API issues**\n\nI’m noticing that the API jar throws NoClassDefFoundError with MailcapCommandMap or MimetypesFileTypeMap constructors. It seems that existing metadata for API 1.2.1 only uses CommandInfo Beans and may avoid com.sun. However, generated tests might target internal SecuritySupport, which could create a coverage gap with missing metadata. If I want to test the API jar on its own, certain operations require the com.sun.activation:jakarta.activation:2.0.0 implementation. Still, adding this dependency could complicate coverage due to potential duplicate classes.\n\n**Inspecting classpath issues**\n\nI’m considering the potential problem of having duplicate classes if both dependencies are on the classpath. With Gradle, if I use testImplementation for both the target and an extra dependency, I need to think about the runtime classpath order. The compile classpath seems to work despite duplicates, but I wonder if a native image might encounter issues with these duplicate classes. I should inspect the com.sun.activation jar to clarify what’s going on there.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b4383382870298b016a4146a78f0081958d6284edf8905249\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQUatXJ7Wa7QsXA6vrGyiMK2TyUL-aC9UI1lyHt9yx-OYa3VufvOQq3wonX68XB74O3ML2jbnzf3wzsZu0yAAq71hsENi0QE73Hpkv8e_XuRM_FACBInBDS-7SCWTqV8-Sch-ISaWsA4sazRrMJsLBbiTSs3Ilg9yFNhMibksJJ0oKD2Xp_uxGj0gHQHAI00nZ0oAeJzFpgWDTZZ7FWJeEup5rv0tIy3SXGuTGpsN1tD6QaZbC5agWYCbGLmC7tppK01HYc3qTsxVHqXWOH9W8YFW2d_e2w59Iz-GkRpITZ7DMOPw-iapsAH61rgscHQjBDugalzO15dVxxnu-zALySB3KCIIbTMvFgVGSaSHiSrNeLP659aYQdzOwjXfIZDgwcKa4j_coTgYrYDaIaZGFVWlB2IJzJNBve7Rs_dZUxoCj6zhtqo_xWW5nJU64lGcdaO0nQ2oOKTy30Sv-8EuIGojIpLKpxS8bWhO5t1GZEEFuMOuNq_YYZ0vi9Ci4OhZZbWdIip2btqNbaVdUfBL7xOdbY7xGtpxqh9KojaYicjQzjwUYL9MKsRyXVsau6jE6gaEneivzWZZp-l9vJzxEIHhB4_FOmB0F5NFm6Qbi0PS1w1IbNhQeMHBm3aDjhr_