intended for compilation without relying on implementation-specific classes. However, for normal use involving registries, it seems I need an additional implementation dependency. This suggests that while no_action might be the initial choice, I should be prepared to adjust based on evidence about the necessity for extra setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Jakarta Activation API 2.0.0 is a compile/API artifact; its POM states it omits implementation-specific classes, while key normal-use classes such as MailcapCommandMap and MimetypesFileTypeMap reference com.sun.activation.registries classes that are not present in the API jar. Meaningful runtime coverage of MIME/mailcap behavior therefore needs the matching implementation artifact on the test classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.sun.activation:jakarta.activation:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides the com.sun.activation.registries implementation classes and default mailcap/mimetypes resources required by normal Jakarta Activation runtime paths that the API jar references but does not include.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For version 2.0.0, generate tests using the jakarta.activation package names, not the pre-2.0 javax.activation imports from the existing 1.2.1 tests. Prefer covering public Jakarta Activation usage such as CommandInfo/CommandObject, DataHandler/DataSource, MailcapCommandMap, and MimetypesFileTypeMap.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"com.sun.activation:jakarta.activation:2.0.0 also contains jakarta.activation classes, so the test classpath will contain duplicate API classes; keep the target jakarta.activation-api dependency present and use the implementation dependency only to supply missing runtime support classes/resources.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative because API-only paths that avoid mailcap/mimetype registries may compile without the implementation but provide limited coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b4383382870298b016a4146bdd9cc8195998f51cb81e93f15\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1718, "output": 884, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34858, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782662835674, "responseId": "resp_0b4383382870298b016a4146b43b888195b04bf5d5d00b0d69"}}
